<div class="instructions">
	<h1>Create a SharePoint farm</h1>
	<p>
		In this example we will create a SharePoint farm. You can get to £50 spend in around 10 
		days with the standard installation, however if you choose high avalibility you will have speant £50 in a few days. 
	</p>

	<ol> 
	<li>Firstly, <a href="https://portal.azure.com/#gallery/Microsoft.SharePointFarm">Click this link</a> to start the processand create the Sharepoint Infrastructure. </li> <li>In the <strong>Create a SharePoint farm</strong> pane, type the name of a resource group.</li> <li>Type a user name and password for a local administrator account on each virtual machine in your farm. Choose a name and password that is difficult to guess, record it, and store it in a secure location.</li> <li>If you want the high-availability farm, click <strong>Enable high availability</strong>.</li> <li>To configure your domain controllers, click the arrow. You can specify a host name prefix (the default is the resource group name), forest root domain name (default is contoso.com), and the size of your domain controllers (default is A1).</li> <li>To configure your SQL servers, click the arrow. You can specify a host name prefix (the default is the resource group name), the size of your SQL servers (default is A5), a database access account name and password (the default is to use the administrator account), and a SQL server service account name (the default is sqlservice) and password (the default is to use the same password as the administrator account).</li> <li>To configure your SharePoint servers, click the arrow. You can specify a host name prefix (the default is the resource group name), the size of your SharePoint servers (default is A2), a SharePoint user account (the default is sp_setup) and password, a SharePoint farm account name (the default is sp_farm) and password, and a SharePoint farm passphrase. The default is to use the administrator password for the SharePoint user account, farm account, and passphrase.</li> <li>To configure optional configuration (the virtual network, storage account, diagnostics), click the arrow.</li> <li>To specify the subscription, click the arrow.</li> <li>When you are done, click <strong>Create</strong>.</li> </ol>
	<p>
		You can find more information about the SharePoint installation over on the <a href="http://azure.microsoft.com/en-us/documentation/articles/virtual-machines-sharepoint-farm-azure-preview/">Azure documentation</a>.
	</p>

